# GitHub Packages — scope only (safe to commit this example)
# Auth token goes in your USER-level file, NOT in the repo:
#   C:\Users\<you>\.npmrc
#
# Option A — token in user .npmrc (simplest, what you already have):
#   @Shashank519915:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
#   //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=ghp_xxxxxxxx
#
# Option B — token via env var (no token in any file):
#   @Shashank519915:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
#   //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}
#   PowerShell before publish/install:
#     $env:GITHUB_TOKEN="ghp_xxxxxxxx"

@Shashank519915:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
